---
/**
 * applied-systems-design-fundamentals · Figure 1 — the HERO "method as a banner".
 *
 * Copied VERBATIM from
 * docs/applied-systems-design/applied-systems-design-fundamentals.html
 * (figure + svg + figcaption). It lives as an .astro component, NOT inline in the
 * MDX, because MDX's JSX parser is unreliable with raw inline SVG that uses
 * kebab-case attributes (text-anchor, font-size, stroke-width, marker-end, …).
 *
 * The source page declared its arrowhead <marker id="arw"> ONCE in a hidden
 * top-of-body <svg defs>. Because each figure is now an isolated component, the
 * #arw marker the HERO references via marker-end="url(#arw)" is inlined here in a
 * local <defs> so it resolves standalone (verbatim from the source defs block).
 */
---

<figure style="margin-top:1.6rem">
    <svg
        viewBox="0 0 640 200"
        role="img"
        aria-label="Five-step design method: Clarify, Estimate, API and data model, High-level design, Deep-dive the bottleneck"
    >
        <defs>
            <marker
                id="arw"
                viewBox="0 0 10 10"
                refX="8.5"
                refY="5"
                markerWidth="7"
                markerHeight="7"
                orient="auto-start-reverse"
                ><path d="M0,0 L10,5 L0,10 z" fill="#6b675f"></path></marker
            >
        </defs>
        <g font-family="ui-sans-serif,system-ui,sans-serif">
            <text
                x="320"
                y="24"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="12"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#111110">THE METHOD — run it in order, out loud, every time</text
            >
            <g>
                <rect
                    x="8"
                    y="56"
                    width="112"
                    height="58"
                    rx="9"
                    fill="#f1eee2"
                    stroke="#7a1f12"
                    stroke-width="1.5"></rect>
                <text
                    x="64"
                    y="80"
                    text-anchor="middle"
                    font-size="12"
                    font-weight="700"
                    fill="#7a1f12">1 Clarify</text
                >
                <text x="64" y="96" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" fill="#6b675f"
                    >funct + non-funct</text
                >
            </g>
            <g>
                <rect x="138" y="56" width="112" height="58" rx="9" fill="#fff" stroke="#1f3a5a"
                ></rect>
                <text
                    x="194"
                    y="80"
                    text-anchor="middle"
                    font-size="12"
                    font-weight="700"
                    fill="#1f3a5a">2 Estimate</text
                >
                <text x="194" y="96" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" fill="#6b675f"
                    >QPS · storage</text
                >
            </g>
            <g>
                <rect x="268" y="56" width="112" height="58" rx="9" fill="#fff" stroke="#d8d4c8"
                ></rect>
                <text
                    x="324"
                    y="80"
                    text-anchor="middle"
                    font-size="11.5"
                    font-weight="700"
                    fill="#111110">3 API + data</text
                >
                <text x="324" y="96" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" fill="#6b675f"
                    >the hot query</text
                >
            </g>
            <g>
                <rect x="398" y="56" width="112" height="58" rx="9" fill="#fff" stroke="#d8d4c8"
                ></rect>
                <text
                    x="454"
                    y="80"
                    text-anchor="middle"
                    font-size="11.5"
                    font-weight="700"
                    fill="#111110">4 Draw it</text
                >
                <text x="454" y="96" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" fill="#6b675f"
                    >boxes &amp; arrows</text
                >
            </g>
            <g>
                <rect x="528" y="56" width="104" height="58" rx="9" fill="#eef5ee" stroke="#2f5d3a"
                ></rect>
                <text
                    x="580"
                    y="80"
                    text-anchor="middle"
                    font-size="11.5"
                    font-weight="700"
                    fill="#2f5d3a">5 Deep-dive</text
                >
                <text x="580" y="96" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" fill="#6b675f"
                    >bottleneck</text
                >
            </g>
            <line x1="120" y1="85" x2="136" y2="85" stroke="#6b675f" marker-end="url(#arw)"></line>
            <line x1="250" y1="85" x2="266" y2="85" stroke="#6b675f" marker-end="url(#arw)"></line>
            <line x1="380" y1="85" x2="396" y2="85" stroke="#6b675f" marker-end="url(#arw)"></line>
            <line x1="510" y1="85" x2="526" y2="85" stroke="#6b675f" marker-end="url(#arw)"></line>
            <text x="320" y="150" text-anchor="middle" font-size="11" fill="#7a1f12"
                >the system changes · the method does not · skipping a step is the #1 failure mode</text
            >
            <text x="320" y="172" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10.5" fill="#6b675f"
                >levers you reuse on every box: cache · replicate · partition · queue · tune
                consistency</text
            >
        </g>
    </svg>
    <figcaption>
        Memorise this banner. The next eight designs are this method applied to a new requirement
        set.
    </figcaption>
</figure>
